Dole ne Amurka ta ninka yawan kudaden da take zubawa a tsarin AI.
Yayin da China ke ci gaba da taka rawa a kan ilimin kere kere, Amurka ta kamata ta ninka kudaden da take zuba wa a fannin bincike, in ji Kai-Fu Lee, wani mai zuba jari da kuma dan kasuwa a fannin AI da ke aiki da Google, Microsoft da Apple.
An yi ta ta yin ta'aziyya bayan da bangarorin gwamnatin tarayya suka yi shelar AI duk da cewa Amurka baki daya ba ta da dabarun amfani da AI.
A wannan bangare kuma, shekarar da ta gabata kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirin da ta yi na kasancewa a kan gaba wajen kirkirar AI nan da shekarar 2030.
"Ƙara kasafin kuɗi na AI zai zama kyakkyawan farawa saboda akwai ƙasashe da yawa da ke bin Amurka sau da yawa kamar yadda muke. Kuma muna neman ci gaba a AI", in ji Lee.
"Samun karin kudi zai iya ninka damar samun babbar nasara a kan ilimin kere kere da za ta faru a Amurka", Lee ya shaidawa CNBC a cikin wata hira da ya yi da shi a wannan makon.
Lee, marubucin littafin nan "AI Superpower: China, Sill Valley and the New World Oder" wanda aka buga a wannan watan ta Houghton Mifflin Harcourt, Shugaba na Sinovation Ventures ya zuba jari tare da daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin AI a China, Face++.
A cikin 1980 a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon ya yi aiki a kan tsarin aiki na AI wanda ya lashe matsayin mafi girma na dan wasan Othello na Amurka kuma daga bisani ya zama babban jami'in Microsoft Research da shugaban kamfanin Google na kasar Sin.
Lee ya yarda da gasa ta fasahar Amurka ta baya-bayan nan kamar Challenge Robotics Challenge na Hukumar Binciken Ci Gaban Tsaro kuma ya tambayi lokacin da zai kasance na gaba don taimakawa wajen gano hangen nesa na gaba.
