Wani ɗalibi a Harvard ya yi nazari a kan yadda za a yi nishaɗi mai kyau
Wani sabon darasi a Harvard a wannan shekara ya ba daliban digiri na biyu isasshen barci don yaƙi da al'adun maza na karatu ta hanyar 'karatun dare' tare da maganin kafeyin.
Wani bincike ya gano cewa ɗalibai a ɗaya daga cikin manyan jami'o'i a duniya suna yin wauta sa'ad da suka zo ga ainihin yadda za su kula da kansu.
Charles Czeisler, Farfesa a fannin kiwon lafiya a Harvard Medical School kuma kwararre a asibitin Brigham da Women's Hospital, ya tsara wani darasi da ya yi imanin shi ne na farko a Amurka.
Bayan ya ba da jawabin da ya nuna amfanin ƙin yin nazari, ya ƙarfafa shi ya soma nazarin.
'A ƙarshen karatun, wata yarinya ta zo wurina kuma ta ce: 'Me ya sa aka gaya mini wannan a wannan lokacin, a shekarata ta ƙarshe?'
Ta ce babu wanda ya taɓa gaya mata game da muhimmancin barci, abin da ya ba ni mamaki,' in ji shi ga jaridar The Telegraph.
Darasi na farko da aka gabatar a wannan shekara ya bayyana wa ɗalibai muhimmancin yin barci mai kyau don inganta aikin ilimi da motsa jiki, da kuma inganta lafiyarsu gaba ɗaya.
Paul Barreira, farfesa a fannin ilimin halayyar dan adam a Harvard Medical School kuma shugaban sashen kula da lafiyar jami'ar, ya ce jami'ar ta yanke shawarar bada shawarar wannan darasi ne bayan ta gano cewa dalibai suna bacci sosai a lokacin da suke makaranta.
An yi wa ɗaliban darussa na tsawon sa'o'i da yawa, har da jerin tambayoyi.
A wani bangare akwai hoton ɗakin kwana, inda ɗalibai ke latsa kofi, zane, kocin da littafi don sanar da tasirin maganin kafeyin da hasken wuta da kuma sakamakon wasan motsa jiki da rashin isasshen bacci da mahimmancin lokacin bacci a matsayin aikin yau da kullun.
A wani ɓangaren kuma, an gaya wa masu halarta yadda barci zai iya ƙara haɗarin ciwon zuciya, hawan jini, baƙin ciki, da kuma ciwon daji.
