HIV/AIDS: China ta ruwaito karuwar sabbin kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14%
China ta yi kiyasin cewa yawan 'yan kasarta da ke rayuwa da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce sama da mutane 820,000 ne suka kamu.
An samu sabbin mutane 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Kusan dukkanin sababbin al'adu suna sadarwa ne ta hanyar jima'i, suna kawo canji daga tsohuwar.
Amma a dā, cutar HIV ta yaɗu da sauri a wasu sassan ƙasar Sin ta hanyar canja jini zuwa jini da ke ɗauke da cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu da kusan rabi, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a birnin Yangon.
A shekara guda, mutane 100,000 ne suke rayuwa da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma ana cewa nuna bambanci ga masu luwadi (LGBT) ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Saboda al'adun ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90% na mazajen da suka yi jima'i da maza za su yi aure da matan.
Yawancin cututtuka da ke fitowa daga rigakafin jima'i ba a cikin waɗannan alaƙar kaɗai ba.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV a duk duniya a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
